e. Heritrix goes through the set of rules in order and for each rule sets t=
he status of the URI being tested to ACCEPT, REJECT, or PASS. At the end of=
 the decide rules, the status in place is the one used, so even if your Mat=
chesListRegexDecideRule rejects the URI, a later rule may change that statu=
s to ACCEPT. For example, your regex might rule out the URI, but if after t=
hat rule you have a TransclusionDecideRule, that &quot;accepts any URI whose pat=
h-from-seed ends in at least one non-navlink hop&quot; (https://webarchive.jira.=
com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Configuring+Crawl+Scope+Using+DecideRules) and is=
 generally used to accept embedded content such as images and videos no mat=
ter the URI pattern, the URI would be ruled back in to acceptance. You coul=
d try moving your MatchesListRegexDecideRule lower in the chain of rules an=
d see if that helps.
